1 MVP

Using the dataset austen_books() from the package janeaustenr:

  1. Find the most common words in both Pride & Prejudice and Sense & Sensibility.


austen_books %>% 
  filter(book %in% c("Sense & Sensibility", "Pride & Prejudice")) %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, text) %>%
  count(word, sort = TRUE)


  1. Find the most common words in both Pride & Prejudice and Sense & Sensibility, not including stop words.


austen_books %>% 
  filter(book %in% c("Sense & Sensibility", "Pride & Prejudice")) %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, text) %>%
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>%
  anti_join(stop_words)


  1. Find the most common sentiment words in both Pride & Prejudice and Sense & Sensibility.


afinn <- austen_books %>% 
  filter(book %in% c("Sense & Sensibility", "Pride & Prejudice")) %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, text) %>%
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>%
  anti_join(stop_words) %>% 
  inner_join(get_sentiments("afinn")) %>% 
  head(10) %>%
  mutate(word = factor(word, 
                       levels = word),
         value = as.factor(value))

afinn
afinn %>% 
  ggplot(aes(y = word, x = n)) + 
  geom_col(aes(fill = value)) +
  labs(x = "Count",
       y = "Common Words",
       title = "Common Words by Sentiment") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

bing <- austen_books %>% 
  filter(book %in% c("Sense & Sensibility", "Pride & Prejudice")) %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, text) %>%
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>%
  anti_join(stop_words) %>% 
  inner_join(get_sentiments("bing")) %>% 
  head(10) %>%
  mutate(word = factor(word, 
                       levels = word))

bing
bing %>% 
ggplot(aes(y = word, x = n)) + 
  geom_col(aes(fill = sentiment)) +
  labs(x = "Count",
       y = "Common Words",
       title = "Common Words by Sentiment") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))


2 Extension

Taking your results above. Can you create a plot which visualises the differences between the books?


austen_books %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, text) %>%
  filter(book %in% c("Sense & Sensibility", "Pride & Prejudice"),
         word %in% c(afinn$word, bing$word)) %>% 
  group_by(book) %>% 
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>%
  mutate(word = factor(word, 
                       levels = word)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(y = word, x = n)) + 
  geom_col(aes(fill = book), position = "dodge") +
  labs(x = "Count",
       y = "Common Words",
       title = "Common Words by Book") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

austen_books %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, text) %>%
  filter(book %in% c("Sense & Sensibility", "Pride & Prejudice"),
         word %in% c(afinn$word)) %>% 
  group_by(book) %>% 
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>%
  mutate(word = factor(word, 
                       levels = word)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(y = word, x = n)) + 
  geom_col(aes(fill = book), position = "dodge") +
  labs(x = "Count",
       y = "Common Words",
       title = "Common Words by Book & Afinn Sentiment") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

austen_books %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, text) %>%
  filter(book %in% c("Sense & Sensibility", "Pride & Prejudice"),
         word %in% c(bing$word)) %>% 
  group_by(book) %>% 
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>%
  mutate(word = factor(word, 
                       levels = word)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(y = word, x = n)) + 
  geom_col(aes(fill = book), position = "dodge") +
  labs(x = "Count",
       y = "Common Words",
       title = "Common Words by Book & Bing Sentiment") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
